Package net.hudup.core

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AccessPoint
    This class is called access point which is used to start modules of Hudup framework.
    Cloneable
    This interface extends the built-in Cloneable, which indicates that any its object can be cloned.
    PluginChangedListener
    PluginStorage manages many RegisterTable (s) and each RegisterTable stores algorithms having the same type.
    PluginManager
    Plug-in manager is responsible for discovering and managing registered recommendation algorithms.
    Transfer
    This interface indicates that any Transfer class which implements it can transfer all built-in variables to other Transfer class via the method Transfer.transfer() without deep copying (deep cloning).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Constants
    This utility final class defines essential constants used over Hudup framework.
    ExtraStorage
    This class is storage to store extra objects besides plug-in storage.
    Firer
    This class is the full implementation of PluginManager.
    PluginChangedEvent
    PluginStorage manages many RegisterTable (s) and each RegisterTable stores algorithms having the same type.
    PluginStorage
    Plug-in manager is responsible for discovering and managing registered recommendation algorithms.
    PluginStorageWrapper
    This class represents wrapper of system plug-in storage.
    RegisterTable
    Plug-in manager is responsible for discovering and managing registered recommendation algorithms.
    RegisterTable.AlgFilter
    This abstract class is used for filtering (selecting) an specified algorithm based on custom criteria.
    RegisterTableList
    This utility class represents a list of RegisterTable (s).
    RegisterTableList.RegisterTableItem
    This class called register table item wraps a register table (RegisterTable).
    Util
    This final class provides important static utility methods to create and initialize essential data structures used over Hudup framework such as Vector, List, Set, Map, and Queue.
